Come listen to me say “I feel like…” a gazillion times on @kenamiphoto podcast! 🙃 Hahaaaa but really, we talk about MY NEW ALBUM and we accidentally announce the TITLE! We also talk about my health, and MOMS IN MUSIC and AGEISM. Lots of good stuff.
Ken and I have known each other since the start of my career and he’s covered a lot of my journey, so it was wonderful to get to chat with him in this new place in my life. 💚
daily reminder that 36 is not old 🌹

ROSE ERA 🌹
My grandma’s name was Rose. My dad’s family graciously passed down her gorgeous “ROSE”necklace to me, given to her by my grandpa sal. (Swipe to see)
Shortly after receiving this necklace, I moved into a house with a rose stained glass window and a single red rose bush planted out front. 
Rose was a great host for every family event when we were kids. And since I’ve moved into this home, I’ve become quite the host as well. I think my kitchen should be called “the rose café”. 
I’m inspired by her daily and feel her calming presence. 🌹 
Miss you nonni rose ❤️
📸 @bridgetism

2022 highlights!!! Got THE BEST new manager, toured for the first time since my remission, finished my 3rd album, made lots of videos, learned a dance routine and danced a lot in general, learned lots of Beatles songs, climbed 700 ft in red rocks and lots of camping, went to fun concerts and best of all went to the motherland Sicily and celebrated our 2 year wedding anniversary. Lots of time with family and dogs and hanging out in our mountain home. 
Happy new year to all of you and hope next year is even better!

I spent my 20s surrounded by men in the music industry. I was in a band of boys, every band we played with was boys, every engineer, record label exec, managers, producers... I love guys and all but at the end of my 20s I realized how much I was missing women in my life and that it was up to me to bring them into my world. 
💚
I’m so SO INSANELY GRATEFUL to get to work with some of the most amazing talented women. You inspire me and lift us ALL up.
💚💜
#womeninmusic

Interview: Ella Vos Shines with Feminine Reclamation in Third Album, ‘SUPERGLUE’ (@ellavos)
—
Singer/songwriter Ella Vos dives headfirst into her intimate, vulnerable, and empowering third full-length album ‘SUPERGLUE,’ a strong testament to finding power and the self.
.
"One of the things I had to reckon with, coming into the music industry, was my own preconceived notions of what a woman in the industry looks like. It’s still very much a man’s world, and it’s hard to undo that thinking." - Ella Vos
.
"I wrote about the mountain and how it makes me feel stronger, and how that’s not vain of me. I think it’s something I’ve really struggled with, being able to see myself as beautiful and not feeling guilty about it."
.
"I’ve stopped trying to think like, ‘I’m gonna think like a man and make things happen!’ – I’m gonna use my feminine strength to do it, and my motherhood skills."
.

I can’t wait for you to hear and see these women shred.

I’m learning to be more aware of my sensitivities and set boundaries and allow myself more rest. 💚 easier said than done! If u didn’t know…
I am an HSP (highly sensitive person)
I am a natural redhead (high sensitivity)
I am a Cancer sun ♋️ and rising (super emotional)
I am a native Californian (needs the sun)
So with all this gloomy weather in LA I have been STRUGGLING!!!!! 
But today the clouds have lifted. 🌞
I find it very hard to be on social media when I’m depressed. It only makes it worse. So I’m spending less time here as I recharge… 
so much has happened since I got back from the microdose tour! 
My son turned 8! I can’t believe it. 
After being in the desert for the Pappy and Harriet’s show, I had a vision of the future that was so clear and direct. I can’t wait to share the new projects I’m working on…

@ellavos is often considered an Indie Pop artist, and while her synth-pop production grounds her in this space, her lyrics and otherworldly vocals clearly transcend the genre. Ella’s music explores motherhood, postpartum depression, reproductive rights, a lymphoma diagnosis and divorce. Ella began in 2016 with her viral hit “White Noise”, which hit number #1 on Spotify’s Viral Charts. 

Acclaimed for her dreamy soundscape, and praised by the likes of @rollingstone and @neongoldrecords , she has received over 300 million streams independently and has sold out shows across North America.
